This paper is primarily focused on object recognition using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the mechanisms of human recognition, which could also fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the combination of multiple trained networks, which could also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
